Subject: [Carpediem] FireFly Music Festival

For the past two years, Dover, DE has held a music festival called FireFly.=
  I went last year and it was insane.  They set up four stages and around 7=
0 bands played over the course of 3 days.  This year, they have extended th=
e festival from 3 to 4 days, added three new stages, and invited over 100 b=
ands.

On December 2nd, they will be selling tickets on sale for CyberMonday.  You=
 can check out past years  at http://fireflyfestival.com/.

I'm already planning on going again but I just wanted to let everyone know =
about the festival.

Jacob

--_000_DA80C3E6C10BE94E8FCACEB239C2FEE401351BB4E10CEXVS01oline_

From Henry.Horsey at students.olin.edu  Wed Dec  4 14:04:24 2013
From: Henry.Horsey at students.olin.edu (Henry Horsey)
Date: Wed, 4 Dec 2013 14:04:24 -0500
Subject: [Carpediem] Charioteers for MannHall Saturday
Message-ID: <9F907DBC-5A48-4B48-BED5-2AD8004EAB04@students.olin.edu>

As Pericles once said, "All good things should flow into the boulevard." This Saturday, MannHall offers a lucky subset of students from the Capital of Olin the opportunity to help funnel citizens of district 13 from the wilds of Swellesley to the boulevard of 2NN. These revered charioteers will receive compensation of 10 dollars an hour should their chariots be provided by the capital, or 15 for those with their own methods of conveyance. The chariots will run from 10:30 to 12:30, and 1:00 to 3:00. Let all those souls with fortitude, ordained for greatness, whom to the call will step forth, be lauded by their comrades and supplicants for the demonstration of commitment to not just this, their great city, but to the greatest of their leader, O' Paricles, for whom the call has been raised. 

Eilon!

From dredfern.olin at gmail.com  Wed Dec  4 15:07:41 2013
From: dredfern.olin at gmail.com (Derek Redfern)
Date: Wed, 4 Dec 2013 15:07:41 -0500
Subject: [Carpediem] Google's #takeaction
Message-ID: <CA+O+WhEw9ddvZLyHX3yM6edWE4UEoNYgbWxya2U_TZOviZAoVw@mail.gmail.com>

--001a11c2538058a0bb04ecbaf86e
Content-Type: multipart/alternative; boundary=001a11c2538058a0b804ecbaf86d

--001a11c2538058a0b804ecbaf86d
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=ISO-8859-1

Google is running a campaign right now to limit how much the government can
snoop on your data. They have a whitehouse.gov petition running until
12/12. Requiring a response from the White House (the minimum required if a
petition is successful) would be a good first step, and I encourage you to
sign the petition if online privacy is important to you.

More information about Google Take Action here:
http://www.google.com/takeaction/ecpa/
Sign the petition here:
https://petitions.whitehouse.gov/petition/reform-ecpa-tell-government-get-warrant/nq258dxk

[image: Inline image 2]

--001a11c2538058a0b804ecbaf86d

"Classic movie night" this Friday night for Olin students. 7:30 pm in the a=
uditorium. The movie will be "3 Days of the Condor." 1975, Robert Redford, =
Faye Dunaway

(I am also inviting some Olin profs/staff-members and other friends who lik=
e classic movies! Should be good fun!)

iCal attached. Come if you can! (But also come to The Sound of Music on ton=
ight! I know it's a lot of movies, but how awesome are movies?)

Tagline: The CIA knows him as Condor. What he knows about them has just mad=
e him an Endangered Species.

Quote from the director (Sidney Pollack): "Basically, we were tryijng to ma=
ke an entertaining thriller that was somehow not unintelligent. We wanted t=
o get rid of the conventional lines in a thriller like, 'Move or I'll blow =
your brains out.' We wanted to get into ideas a little more serious than th=
at."

Thanks, Caitrin

t also come to The Sound of Music on tonight! I know it's a lot of movies, =
but how awesome are movies?)</div><div><br></div><div><div><i>Tagline</i>: =
The CIA knows him as Condor. What he knows about them has just made him an =
Endangered Species.</div><div><br></div><div><i>Quote from the director (Si=
dney Pollack):</i>&nbsp;"Basically, we were tryijng to make an entertaining=
 thriller that was somehow not unintelligent. We wanted to get rid of the c=
onventional lines in a thriller like, 'Move or I'll blow your brains out.' =
We
 wanted to get into ideas a little more serious than that."</div></div><div=
><br></div><div>Thanks, Caitrin</div></div><div><br></div></body></html>

--_000_CEC5E946790F3caitrinlyncholinedu_--

nity to learn more about taking language courses at Wellesley!

rsday December 5th, 12:30 - 1:30 in the dining hall. iCal attached.

Longer: The AHS faculty members are hosting a Languages Lunch in the dining=
 hall on Thursday, December 5th from 12:30 to 1:30. Lunch time information =
session about some of the language courses offered at Wellesley.  Come meet=
 Wellesley professors who teach Russian, Swahili, Hindi, Japanese, Korean, =
Chinese, and possibly others.  Bring your own lunch, main floor of the dini=
ng hall.  Look for Caitrin Lynch.

ucts Real Markets, and we hope you like them too!

f technical precision and creative intricacy in our laser-cut cards. The bu=
tterflies adorning these cards are cut from premium cardstock and given a b=
acking to support the delicacy of the design. All of our products are hand-=
assembled by design engineers from Olin College and are only available duri=
ng this holiday season. Order today for yourself or for someone you want to=
 impress!

-Sharon and Liz

Just a note for anyone who uses amazon. www.smile.amazon.com<http://www.smi=
le.amazon.com> is essentially the same as amazon.com, but it donates someth=
ing like .5% of all profits to charity! It doesn't sound like very much, bu=
t I'm sure it adds up.
Use it :)

From: Emily Fox-Penner [mailto:efoxpenner at college.harvard.edu]

Subject: Climate Action this Sunday

Hey Olin! Even if you don't have a divest campaign, the goal of our action =
tomorrow is to strengthen the connections between campuses and it would be =
great to see Olin represented...
Tomorrow,
Join DIVEST HARVARD<https://www.facebook.com/divestharvard>, Fossil Free <h=
ttp://fossilfreemit.org> MIT<http://www.fossilfreemit.org/>, Tufts<http://t=
uftsdivest.com/> Divest<http://tuftsdivest.com>, and students from Boston U=
niversity, Boston College, Wellesley, Northeastern, Brandeis, and UMass, as=
 well as 350 Mass.<http://350ma.org/>
for a massive campus climate movement-building convergence
and the largest collective action in support of fossil fuel divestment<http=
://gofossilfree.org/> in the country!
We'll meet at 1 PM at the John W. Weeks Footbridge<https://maps.google.com/=
maps?safe=3Doff&ie=3DUTF-8&q=3DJohn+W.+Weeks+Bridge&fb=3D1&gl=3Dus&hq=3Dj+w=
eeks+bridge&cid=3D13583175244199495737&ei=3DyH2dUtP_FoHKsQSjvYKYAQ&ved=3D0C=
J4BEPwSMAs> over the Charles River for a short rally featuring Tim DeChrist=
opher<http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=3D_TtewHymN2g> and a couple of other s=
tudent speakers.
Then we will drop our 15'x70' banner from the bridge before marching to our=
 respective campuses to kick off a national call for divestment.
 Divestment is our institutions' opportunity to live up to their mission st=
atements and lead on the climate crisis. As MLK said, "in this unfolding co=
nundrum of life and history, there is such a thing as being too late." Whil=
e our administrations stall, people continue to suffer from environmental i=
njustice and the climate spirals out of control. Let's be on the right side=
 of history this Sunday.

RSVP<https://docs.google.com/a/college.harvard.edu/forms/d/1NIECoDewmRzvPGy=
zJ5MW-kswIilol5Yhi17djKF_K4U/viewform> or contact Emily (Harvard '17) efoxp=
enner at college.harvard.edu<mailto:efoxpenner at college.harvard.edu> or Henney =
(Harvard '15) henneysullivan at gmail.com<mailto:henneysullivan at gmail.com> wit=
h questions

Hi Carpe!

Looking for awesome Holiday gifts? Seen our ornaments on the WH3 tree? Take=
 a look at HexGears<www.hexgears.com>, a sleek product that Kevin and I mad=
e for our Real Products, Real Markets class at Olin.

[cid:image001.jpg at 01CEF424.0CE61B90][cid:image002.jpg at 01CEF424.0CE61B90][ci=
d:image003.jpg at 01CEF424.0CE61B90]

They're modular hexagons with embedded planetary gears, and each HexGear ha=
s its own custom, laser-engraved design. We make them right here at Olin, a=
nd they're really fun to spin around. They make beautiful ornaments and per=
fects gifts for the mechanically inclined person in your life.

Anything you order will be delivered before Christmas, and all proceeds go =
directly to Olin.

Check them out at HexGears.com<www.hexgears.com>, and be sure to tell your =
friends and family all about them!

All the best,
Julianne and Kevin

Hey homies,

One of my Babson friends (the cool kind of Babbie) is putting together a pr=
oduction of the Vagina Monologues that is showing in February. You should b=
e in it! Check out below for more info.

<3  Casey

From: Lin, Elizabeth [mailto:elin1 at babson.edu]
Sent: Sunday, December 08, 2013 11:01 PM
To: Casey Monahan


Vagina Monologues was developed by Eve Ensler in response to the silence, s=
tigma, and violence surrounding people with vaginas. She conducted intervie=
ws around the nation and turned those interviews into the Vagina Monologues=
. It's a part of a larger organization she runs called V-Day, which I've li=
nked here. http://www.vday.org/home

We're holding auditions on December 11th and 13th at 9pm in Babson Hall 203=
. You only have to attend one date, there's no preparation necessary (You'l=
l just be reading for a few minutes tops). If you're sure you want to be a =
part of it and you can't make either date, I can also arrange for you to re=
ad for me outside of these dates.


On Sun, Dec 8, 2013 at 10:56 PM, Lin, Elizabeth <elin1 at babson.edu<mailto:el=
in1 at babson.edu>> wrote:




--
Lizzie Lin
Babson College Class of 2015
Presidential Scholar
Babson Women's Rugby President & Forwards Captain

So it's time for auditions for next semester's FWOP show! The show will be =
"A Funny Thing Happened on the Way to the Forum". It's a musical, so everyo=
ne should be really excited for all the singing and dancing you get to do! =
Auditions will be held Saturday December 14 starting at 3:00 pm.

If you have ever considered trying out for musical theater now would be an =
awesome opportunity do to so, because we need as many people as possible, a=
nd as this show is a comedy, it will be tons of fun.


Audition materials are attached to this email:
Everyone must come prepared to sing one of the following songs, as well as =
ready to perform every script segment of your gender.

I look forward to seeing you all there!



Song Options:
Comedy tonight-  Pseudolus: baritone
Love I Hear- Hero: tenor
Lovely- Philia: soprano
Dirty old Man- Domina: Mezzo



Script Segments:
Philia: Female
Hero: Male
Pseudolus: Male
Prologus: Male


--_000_DA80C3E6C10BE94E8FCACEB239C2FEE401351BE1F181EXVS01oline_

TLDR: Help us teach 3rd graders about motors during finals week

Hey Carpe,

So for our E&M project, Rahil and I are teaching a lesson about motors to 3=
rd graders at Westwood Elementary School. We're going in at 3 times, Tuesda=
y (the 17th) from 9-11, and Thursday (the 19th) from 9-11 and then from 12:=
30 - 2:30.

We would love for some of you to accompany us to help out, especially while=
 the students are doing the lab in which they will be building a simple mot=
or. Please let us know if you would like to come for one or more of the tim=
es!

It should be a lot of fun!

Thanks,
Rahil and Jamie


Jamie Gorson | Class of 2016

From las at olin.edu  Mon Dec  9 13:24:09 2013
From: las at olin.edu (Lynn Andrea Stein)
Date: Mon, 9 Dec 2013 13:24:09 -0500
Subject: [Carpediem] Semester in Brazil?
Message-ID: <3B3937EE-D893-4B71-ABED-36747A232674@olin.edu>

--Apple-Mail=_DC222345-1C4F-4F9D-AF93-5FC306F9A74C
Content-Transfer-Encoding: quoted-printable
Content-Type: text/plain; charset="us-ascii"

Dear students (and please circulate this to others; I figured this was a =
better place to post than students at lists, but meant for this to be =
genuinely open):

You may be aware that we are working with Insper, a business school in =
Sao Paulo, Brazil, to help them develop a new engineering program =
launching in early 2015.  Our partners at Insper have expressed interest =
in having some Olin students spend time helping them to develop their =
new engineering curriculum.  One idea that's been tossed around is a =
semester-long residency in spring 2014.  This is obviously *very* soon =
and would likely require your taking LOA from Olin (yes, I know the =
date's passed, but magic may be possible).  This would likely involve =
becoming a junior member of their curriculum-and-culture design team, =
including helping to design and run some candidates' weekend type =
activities.  You should assume that your expenses for the semester would =
be covered.

If you might be interested in doing this, please contact me ASAP so that =
we can talk.

Thanks!

Lynn

p.s. Other opportunities may be possible summer/fall, so you can let me =
know about interest in that as well.  My focus right now is on figuring =
out whether Spring 2014 is viable.=

--Apple-Mail=_DC222345-1C4F-4F9D-AF93-5FC306F9A74C

From: carpediem-bounces at lists.olin.edu [mailto:carpediem-bounces at lists.olin=
.edu] On Behalf Of Jamie Gorson
Sent: Monday, December 09, 2013 12:07 PM
To: carpediem at lists.olin.edu
Subject: [Carpediem] Teach 3rd Graders about motors!

TLDR: Help us teach 3rd graders about motors during finals week

Hey Carpe,

So for our E&M project, Rahil and I are teaching a lesson about motors to 3=
rd graders at Westwood Elementary School. We're going in at 3 times, Tuesda=
y (the 17th) from 9-11, and Thursday (the 19th) from 9-11 and then from 12:=
30 - 2:30.

We would love for some of you to accompany us to help out, especially while=
 the students are doing the lab in which they will be building a simple mot=
or. Please let us know if you would like to come for one or more of the tim=
es!

It should be a lot of fun!

Thanks,
Rahil and Jamie


Jamie Gorson | Class of 2016
Leading the Revolution in Engineering Education

F.I.L.M. Club and Danish "Klub" Present: The Hunt<http://www.youtube.com/wa=
tch?v=3DieLIOBkMgAQ>

[cid:image002.jpg at 01CEF5B2.3CF9C9F0]

The Hunt (Jagten in Danish) is a 2012 Danish drama film directed by Thomas =
Vinterberg. Vinterberg is famous for directing Festen, the first film to be=
 categorized under the Dogme 95 filmmaking movement. The Hunt is thematical=
ly very similar to Festen with both films dealing with child abuse.

(Jagten in Danish) is a 2012 Danish drama film directed by Thomas Vinterber=

Babson is doing shows in the spring!

The Babson Players (who just put on Little Shop of Horrors and Legally Blon=
de last spring) are putting on the hit musical...

[cid:image001.png at 01CEF5B6.B1DAE9D0]

Auditions will be next semester, January 26-27th.

That's all I know for now, just save the dates! (You only need to go to one=
 day of auditions).

I'm also letting you know now so that you don't commit yourselves to other =
things because musicals > life.





Note: They will be needing lots of people, especially dancers. Even if you =
don't dance or have never done a show before, I highly encourage you to aud=
ition!

The spring show always accepts more people than the fall show, so you shoul=
d audition if you are interested. The Babson Players is a group full of rea=
lly awesome people!


Brian Liebson


PS I'll be sending another email next semester with more specific details.

 cost about $20 a person. <o:p></o:p></p><p class=3DMsoNormal><o:p>&nbsp;</=

ms/d/1JR_4GfjewWAJJLO_RkFiy1nlsX1p1xiyzbN0sh2rkOg/edit</a><o:p></o:p></p><p=

Tldr; Do you want to split MDF shipping costs w/ me?


Do you want a big honking piece of MDF? I do. A 1/8th inch thick big honkin=
g piece of MDF, actually. Who wouldn't?

This website has large pieces of MDF. It is a crappy website, but the MDF i=
s cheap and I'm told it is good quality.
http://www.woodnshop.com/Hardwood/MEDIUM_DENSITY.htm

You can do lots of things with a big honking piece of MDF, including laser =
cut things out of it for fun/class/profit, bandsaw things out of it for fun=
/class/profit, use it as a sled or very large Frisbee, I'm sure you can thi=
nk of something good. Maybe you will prank a friend and replace their door/=
bed/roommate with a big honking piece of MDF. Stranger things have happened=
.

Shipping on the piece I want (4'x8', 1.8", $5.00) is approximately
                1 piece  -              $12
                2 pieces -             $14
                3 pieces -             $18... and so on

If you want to order a big honking piece of MDF with me, tell me! Even if y=
ours is not the same size as mine, I'll bet the shipping will be better. Sa=
ve up for the next passionate pursuit/random I-wanna-laser-cut-something bi=
nge/PoE project!

Yours,
Eric


At first I considered inserting a picture, then I realized that a big wood-=
tinted rectangle was essentially the same thing. Enjoy.

tarting at 8pm Friday, Saturday and Sunday (iCal attached)

Are you expecting a long weekend full of studying? Or a long weekend full o=
f other fun stuff? Will you need some coffee and baked goods to keep you go=
ing?

The library has you covered. Come to the library after 8pm Friday, Saturday=
 and Sunday for delicious hot coffee and even more delicious baked goods. B=
ring your group meeting to the library to take advantage of the snacks, or =
swing by before or after Expresso or the PowerChords concert.

Content-Type: text/plain; charset="us-ascii"
Content-Transfer-Encoding: quoted-printable

If you need to share documents with more than one other person, you can jus=
t give everyone the password to one of the accounts that it is shared with =
and have them edit it from that account.

Life Hack.

If you need to share documents with more than one other person, you can jus=
t give everyone the password to one of the accounts that it is shared with =
and have them edit it from that account.

Life Hack.

From las at olin.edu  Thu Dec 12 18:10:52 2013
From: las at olin.edu (Lynn Andrea Stein)
Date: Thu, 12 Dec 2013 18:10:52 -0500
Subject: [Carpediem] Resolved:  Semester in Brazil?
In-Reply-To: <3B3937EE-D893-4B71-ABED-36747A232674@olin.edu>
References: <3B3937EE-D893-4B71-ABED-36747A232674@olin.edu>
Message-ID: <99E5E09B-CE0C-437E-BA51-DB699BABF74F@olin.edu>

--_000_99E5E09BCE0C437EBA51DB699BABF74Folinedu_
Content-Type: text/plain; charset="us-ascii"
Content-Transfer-Encoding: quoted-printable

Dear Insper-interested students,

I'm sorry to let you know that we're not going to proceed with the spring 2=
014 Olin-student-LOA in Sao Paulo.  Student interest has been fantastic, an=
d this decision is not being made for lack of Olin enthusiasm.  The Insper =
folks also really enjoyed their interactions with Olin students while here.=
  However, given the short time frame, the significant complexities involve=
d, and the results of our intense explorations in the past few days, we sim=
ply don't feel that we can pull off what is necessary to make a good use of=
 your time.

At this point, we *do* expect to proceed with some sort of summer experienc=
e.  We've already started preliminary discussions, and we'll get to serious=
 work on it shortly.  We we will be sure to let you know when we have more =
information about what that might look like.  There's also a possibility of=
 other activities taking place at other times, and of course we'll let you =
know about those as well.

Thanks for your interest and your patience.

Lynn and the Olin/Insper team

On Dec 9, 2013, at 1:24 PM, Lynn Andrea Stein <las at olin.edu<mailto:las at olin=
.edu>> wrote:

Dear students (and please circulate this to others; I figured this was a be=
tter place to post than students at lists, but meant for this to be genuinely =
open):

You may be aware that we are working with Insper, a business school in Sao =
Paulo, Brazil, to help them develop a new engineering program launching in =
early 2015.  Our partners at Insper have expressed interest in having some =
Olin students spend time helping them to develop their new engineering curr=
iculum.  One idea that's been tossed around is a semester-long residency in=
 spring 2014.  This is obviously *very* soon and would likely require your =
taking LOA from Olin (yes, I know the date's passed, but magic may be possi=
ble).  This would likely involve becoming a junior member of their curricul=
um-and-culture design team, including helping to design and run some candid=
ates' weekend type activities.  You should assume that your expenses for th=
e semester would be covered.

If you might be interested in doing this, please contact me ASAP so that we=
 can talk.

Thanks!

Lynn

p.s. Other opportunities may be possible summer/fall, so you can let me kno=
w about interest in that as well.  My focus right now is on figuring out wh=
ether Spring 2014 is viable.
_______________________________________________
Carpediem mailing list
Carpediem at lists.olin.edu<mailto:Carpediem at lists.olin.edu>
https://lists.olin.edu/mailman/listinfo/carpediem


--_000_99E5E09BCE0C437EBA51DB699BABF74Folinedu_

It's been too long since midnight math has happened, so that's changing ton=
ight. Put on your argyle sweater, pop on up to WH4, and listen to some wond=
erfully mathematical musings. Zach Del Rosario, in his infinite wisdom, wil=
l be giving a lecture about numerical methods in linear algebra. He'll tell=
 us all about how mathematicians make their matrix multiplications go (in t=
he words of Eric Van Wyk) screaming-nasty fast. There will be cheese, there=
 will be crackers, there will be punch, and as always, classy attire is hig=
hly encouraged.

Discretely,
The Midnight Mathematicians

As a reminder, this needs to happen by 12:00 noon today. We are supposed to=
 park in the bottom three tiers of Lot A or in Lot C.



Here's the original facilities email:


"Subject: Saturday Snow Event Parking Notification

Good Morning,


In preparation for the winter storm approaching Saturday Dec 14, we are req=
uesting that we implement Snow Emergency parking to assist with the snow re=
moval efforts.   All motor vehicles must be moved to Lot A (rows 4, 5 and 6=
) or Lot C by 12:00 PM Saturday Dec 14.  We are asking for Members of the c=
ommunity who are leaving a vehicle on campus, to park in these designated S=
now Emergency parking areas (Lot A, rows 4, 5 and 6 or Lot C).

Student parking in Lot A (rows 1, 2 or 3); Lot B-2, or Lot D is prohibited =
after 12:00 PM Saturday Dec 14.   Students are to park in the designated Sn=
ow Emergency parking areas (Lot A, rows 4, 5 and 6 or Lot C).

Thank you for your cooperation

Russ Zacharias

Director of Facilities
Olin College of Engineering
781-292-2317

- Getting Started in Electronics book (really great! Covers all the circuit things in ModCon and RWM and more, with pictures!), $5
- Troubleshooting Analog Circuits (required for EE Proto), $10
- Controls Textbook for Lundberg, $30
- Discrete Mathematics with Ducks (required for Discrete), $10
- Designing for Interaction (required for HFID I think, all about interface design), $10

~Molly

Have a few hours of free time tomorrow? Want to get into Boston? Feel like =
helping out a charity for the homeless? If so, I have just the thing for yo=
u.

I run a non-profit called The Simple Things that provides toiletries to the=

morrow. We would need about an hour or two of your time to help bagging ite=
ms and transporting. It is fun and not difficult work.

You would be traveling into downtown Boston, right next to the Park Street =
T station.

Let me know if you are interested. We need your help!

the recent films have been relatively depressing, I have to show a not-so-d=
epressing film this week. This is from James Gunn, the director of Slither =
and the upcoming Guardians of the Galaxy. If people are interested in watch=
ing something else, Perks of Being a Wallflower and Future Folk are potenti=
al candidates.

John Arakaki, F.I.L.M. Director
Amanda Lee, 96 Minutes Run Time
Kris Groth, Lots of Snacks
Philicia Chow, Key Grip

From: Eric Kolker <eric.kolker at students.olin.edu>
Date: Tuesday, October 30, 2012 3:00 AM
To: "carpediem at lists.olin.edu" <carpediem at lists.olin.edu>
Subject: Re: [Carpediem] Who's awake?

 

Hello again, Carpe. It's been far too long, hasn't it?

 

Let me also take this opportunity to answer the FAQ: 

 

WTFBBQ, Kolker? Why?

It's for shits and giggles +/- science. .so this isn't part of a study or
anything, but if I get bored I may make a few graphs of average number of
replies, most consistent repliers, etc.

 

.but seriously, why are you up that late?

Usually it's MADVLSI. The course's workload operates on a 1/14th duty cycle
with a two week period and a pulse amplitude of ~12 hours.

 

Do you sleep?

Usually, but experience shows I can run on consistent, small integer
multiples of 90-minute REM cycles for a few days on end.

 

What's the least you've slept in a week?

I think my record latest weekly average bedtime is around 6AM, but that
includes an all-nighter. There's probably a correlation to sleep in there
somewhere.

 

Am I failing ModCon?

No comment.

 

Thanks!

~e

Subject: Re: [Carpediem] Who's awake?

Hello again, Carpe. It's been far too long, hasn't it?

Let me also take this opportunity to answer the FAQ:

WTFBBQ, Kolker? Why?
It's for shits and giggles +/- science. ...so this isn't part of a study or=
 anything, but if I get bored I may make a few graphs of average number of =
replies, most consistent repliers, etc.

...but seriously, why are you up that late?
Usually it's MADVLSI. The course's workload operates on a 1/14th duty cycle=
 with a two week period and a pulse amplitude of ~12 hours.

Do you sleep?
Usually, but experience shows I can run on consistent, small integer multip=
les of 90-minute REM cycles for a few days on end.

What's the least you've slept in a week?
I think my record latest weekly average bedtime is around 6AM, but that inc=
ludes an all-nighter. There's probably a correlation to sleep in there some=
where.

Am I failing ModCon?
No comment.

Thanks!
~e

Hello again, Carpe. It's been far too long, hasn't it?

Let me also take this opportunity to answer the FAQ:

WTFBBQ, Kolker? Why?
It's for shits and giggles +/- science. ...so this isn't part of a study or=
 anything, but if I get bored I may make a few graphs of average number of =
replies, most consistent repliers, etc.

...but seriously, why are you up that late?
Usually it's MADVLSI. The course's workload operates on a 1/14th duty cycle=
 with a two week period and a pulse amplitude of ~12 hours.

Do you sleep?
Usually, but experience shows I can run on consistent, small integer multip=
les of 90-minute REM cycles for a few days on end.

What's the least you've slept in a week?
I think my record latest weekly average bedtime is around 6AM, but that inc=
ludes an all-nighter. There's probably a correlation to sleep in there some=
where.

Am I failing ModCon?
No comment.

Thanks!
~e

Subject: Re: [Carpediem] Who's awake?

Hello again, Carpe. It's been far too long, hasn't it?

Let me also take this opportunity to answer the FAQ:

WTFBBQ, Kolker? Why?
It's for shits and giggles +/- science. ...so this isn't part of a study or=
 anything, but if I get bored I may make a few graphs of average number of =
replies, most consistent repliers, etc.

...but seriously, why are you up that late?
Usually it's MADVLSI. The course's workload operates on a 1/14th duty cycle=
 with a two week period and a pulse amplitude of ~12 hours.

Do you sleep?
Usually, but experience shows I can run on consistent, small integer multip=
les of 90-minute REM cycles for a few days on end.

What's the least you've slept in a week?
I think my record latest weekly average bedtime is around 6AM, but that inc=
ludes an all-nighter. There's probably a correlation to sleep in there some=
where.

Am I failing ModCon?
No comment.

Thanks!
~e

> cycle with a two week period and a pulse amplitude of ~12 hours.

>

> multiples of 90-minute REM cycles for a few days on end.

From Gregory.Edelston at students.olin.edu  Fri Dec 27 23:49:43 2013
From: Gregory.Edelston at students.olin.edu (Gregory Edelston)
Date: Fri, 27 Dec 2013 23:49:43 -0500
Subject: [Carpediem] songwriting group? [vague]
Message-ID: <DA80C3E6C10BE94E8FCACEB239C2FEE4013547F4AF8C@EXVS01.olin.edu>

--_000_DA80C3E6C10BE94E8FCACEB239C2FEE4013547F4AF8CEXVS01oline_
Content-Type: text/plain; charset="us-ascii"
Content-Transfer-Encoding: quoted-printable

I wish I wrote more songs. I've felt that way for several years. I've tried=
 to get into it every now and again, and I've never quite gotten the moment=
um I want.

To that end, I wonder if a songwriting group might be useful/fun. We could =
have a different prompt each week, and everyone has to write a song with th=
at theme. No specified format, as long as you write something. At the end o=
f the week, we could share our songs with each other if you're comfortable =
with it, or you could just keep it for yourself. These songs would not be e=
xpected to be anywhere near good - my dad says he's not proud of his first =
300 or so. (Also, my dad is awesome.)

The format is super-flexible right now. It could be an actual club that mee=
ts weekly, or just a mailing list, or whatever other format you can think o=
f. Nothing is set in stone. If you're interested, shoot me a line! I'd love=
 to hear your input, because this is something that is important to me, and=
 I suspect that it's important to many of you, too. Let's make this happen,=
 and let's make it awesome.

Love,
Greg

--_000_DA80C3E6C10BE94E8FCACEB239C2FEE4013547F4AF8CEXVS01oline_

From William.Saulnier at students.olin.edu  Sat Dec 28 23:02:11 2013
From: William.Saulnier at students.olin.edu (William Saulnier)
Date: Sat, 28 Dec 2013 23:02:11 -0500
Subject: [Carpediem] The Music of 2013
Message-ID: <DA80C3E6C10BE94E8FCACEB239C2FEE4013547513703@EXVS01.olin.edu>

Hello friends,

I had an idea. As the year comes to a close, why don't you join me and the rest of Olin in picking the songs that defined 2013 for you. Not restricted to songs that came out in 2013, they should be songs that either represent 2013 to you, or were just something that you jammed out to during the year. Let's ring in the new year with all of the songs that made 2013 what it was.

Here's a link to the playlist on spotify. I look forward to everyone's additions!

http://open.spotify.com/user/lego6245/playlist/5TzPtazcGFNj5tSrdrTyxo

-William

From: Celine.Ta at students.olin.edu (Celine Ta)
Date: Mon, 30 Dec 2013 16:03:22 -0500
Subject: [Carpediem] $18K to Student Founders
Message-ID: <DA80C3E6C10BE94E8FCACEB239C2FEE4013547F4B0E6@EXVS01.olin.edu>

--_000_DA80C3E6C10BE94E8FCACEB239C2FEE4013547F4B0E6EXVS01oline_
Content-Type: text/plain; charset="us-ascii"
Content-Transfer-Encoding: quoted-printable

While researching summer opportunities, I came across the Summer at Highland (=
http://summer.hcp.com//<http://summer.hcp.com/>) program on Olin's (admitte=
dly outdated) PGP site. The program still looks like it's up and running, s=
o I thought I'd send out a reminder of its existence. It's seems like an ap=
propriate space to the bridge the gap between product and firm, if you want=
 to take an idea a little further beyond what an Olin E! course can go.

The program offers an $18K stipend (=3D you don't have to pay it back), off=
ice space, and resources to student teams that want to develop a product id=
ea over 10 weeks. Note: This is an accelerator, so ideally, some validation=
 has already been done (i.e. prototypes, market research, etc.).

Hey you.

Yeah, you.

You should join some mailing lists.

https://lists.olin.edu/mailman/listinfo

It's good for you, for email culture at Olin, and for people who like email=
ing groups of people at Olin who share interests.

(For example: If, perchance, you've watched a bunch of Doctor Who over brea=
k on Netflix and you think you'd be interested in hanging out with other Wh=
ovians when it's not break, the TARDIS list is welcoming you with open arms=
!)

(Or maybe you want to join some other club! Have you taken an interest in b=
aking recently? What about movies? Decided you want to join Sailbot? All of=
 these are open to you!)

(Or you could try something completely new, like Ham Radio or answering sur=
veys over on Askme)

(Or whatever. There are more than 200 lists. Join one. Or two. Or all of th=
em.)

New year =3D new lists.
